The '''New England Foundation for the Arts''' (NEFA), headquartered in [[Boston, Massachusetts|Boston]], [[Massachusetts]], is one of six [[Non-profit organization|not-for-profit]] [[Regional arts council (RAO)|regional arts organization]]s funded by the [[National Endowment for the Arts]] (NEA) and by private foundations, corporations and individuals.
Founded in 1976, NEFA functions as a grantmaker, program initiator, regional laboratory, project coordinator, developer of resources, and builder of creative partnerships among artists, arts organizations, and funders.<ref>[http://www.usregionalarts.org/docs/research/SAF-Survey%20RepoNAL%20VERSION.pdf A Survey and Analysis of Regional Traditional Arts Programs and Services] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080724153456/http://www.usregionalarts.org/docs/research/SAF-Survey%20RepoNAL%20VERSION.pdf |date=2008-07-24 }}</ref> The Foundation serves the state [[arts council]]s of [[Connecticut]], [[Maine]], [[Massachusetts]], [[New Hampshire]], [[Rhode Island]], and [[Vermont]], which comprise [[New England]]. NEFA also has national programs in contemporary dance and [[Native American art|Native arts]], and has partnered on several international dance programs.
