'''Sang Bleu''' ({{IPA-fr| s ɑ̃bl ø}}) is an independent, multi-disciplinary media platform and creative agency encompassing ''Sang Bleu'' magazine, a publication centred around contemporary art, culture, fashion, fine art, [[performance art]], literature, [[sociology]], kink and tattooing;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sangbleu.com/ |title=Sang Bleu |publisher= |location= |accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hebdo.ch/hebdo/projecteurs/detail/tatouage-zurich-du-sang-bleu-dans-les-veines |title=Tatouage: Zurich a du Sang Bleu dans les veines |publisher=[[L'Hebdo]] |author= |date=26 May 2016}}</ref> SangBleu, a typeface under the type design company Swiss Typeface and a creative agency called Sang Bleu. Sang Bleu was initiated in 2006 in [[London]], UK, by Maxime Plescia-Büchi, its Swiss creative director, who currently runs it with his wife Hope Plescia-Büchi. Büchi performs as a tattoo artist at Sang Bleu London together with a dozen other tattoo artists and temporary resident artists. Sang Bleu is notable for its publications,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://hypebeast.com/2016/4/maxime-buchi-of-sang-bleu-releases-a-book-of-his-1000-tattoo-designs |title= Maxime Buchi of Sang Bleu Releases a Book of His 1000 Tattoo Designs |publisher=HypeBeast |author= Kevin Wong |date=18 April 2016 }}</ref> its collaboration with [[Switzerland|Swiss]] [[Luxury goods|luxury]] [[watchmaker]] [[Hublot]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hublot.com/en/news/hublot-has-sang-bleu-in-its-veins |title= Hublot has Sang Bleu In Its Veins |publisher=Hublot |author= Mark Bernardo |date=22 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.montres-de-luxe.com/Hublot-Big-Bang-Sang-Bleu_a11505.html |title=Hublot Big Bang Sang Bleu |publisher=Montres de Luxe |location= |date=}}</ref> and its work on celebrities like [[Kanye West]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://uk.complex.com/style/2015/02/maxime-buchi-sang-bleu-kanye-west-interview |title=Maxime Buchi Talks Tattooing Kanye West, Sang Bleu, and His New London Shop |publisher=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]] |location= |date= 28 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2092923/tattoo-kanye-west-maxime-buchi/ |title=What's It Like To Tattoo Kanye West? |publisher=[[MTV News]] |author= Andres Tardio |date=28 February 2013}}</ref> and [[FKA Twigs]]. Sang Bleu is also known for creating logos and corporate typefaces for Balenciaga, Rick Owens, CSS Bard Hessel Museum, the City of Stockholm, Esquire magazine and Vogue.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://amuse-i-d.vice.com/a-tattoo-is-for-life-not-just-for-hipsters/ |title=Sang Bleu: Ink Outside the Box |publisher=Amuse |author=Laura Hawkins |date=28 May 2016}}</ref> It has held events at department stores including [[Selfridges]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dazeddigital.com/artsandculture/article/20186/1/maxime-buchis-tattoo-revolution-comes-to-selfridges |title=Maxime Buchi's tattoo revolution comes to Selfridges |publisher=Dazed |location= |author=Claire Marie Healy |date=2015}}</ref> the [[Metropolitan Life Insurance Company Tower|London Edition Hotel]] and Imperial Art Studios in [[Downtown Los Angeles]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://amadeusmag.com/blog/sang-bleu-art-tattoo-pop-up-at-imperial-art-studios/ |title=Sang Bleu Art & Tattoo Pop-Up At Imperial Art Studios |publisher=Amadeus Magazine |location=Los Angeles, CA |accessdate=}}</ref> In May 2016, the first international Sang Bleu studio opened in [[Zürich]], [[Switzerland]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.friday-magazine.ch/ro/2016/05/28/lantre-de-lencre.html |title=L'Antre de l'Encre |publisher=Friday Magazine |author=Emmanuel Coissy |date=28 May 2016}}</ref>
