{{Infobox Artwork | image_file=St. James led to his execution.jpg | image_size=200px | title=St. James Led to His Execution | artist=Andrea Mantegna | year=c. 1455 | height_metric= | width_metric= | height_imperial= | width_imperial= | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in | museum= |city= }}
'''''St. James Led to His Execution''''' was a painting by [[Andrea Mantegna]]. It was destroyed on March 11, 1944, when the [[Ovetari Chapel]] in [[Padua]] was bombed by the Allies during [[World War II]].
The [[British Museum]] owns a preparatory drawing for the painting.
[[File:Study for St. James led to his execution.jpg|left|thumb|Preparatory drawing for ''St. James Led to His Execution'']] {{Andrea Mantegna}}
